President Donald Trump has declared a major disaster in the state of Louisiana due to severe storms and tornadoes that occurred in April 2019. Federal assistance will be provided to supplement state and local recovery efforts in the affected areas. This assistance includes funding for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Traci L. Brasher has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for the recovery operations. Additional designations may be made in the future based on further damage assessments. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA News Desk.